  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Universal?",
  "response": "Starting a new job at Universal can be exciting and a bit overwhelming. Here are some things new employees should know going into their first day:\n\n1. **Dress Code**: Make sure you understand the company's dress code. Universal typically has specific guidelines, especially if you are working in a customer-facing role or in the parks. Business casual is usually a safe bet for your first day unless instructed otherwise.\n\n2. **Arrival Time**: Plan to arrive early. Being punctual is important and will give you a buffer for any unexpected delays. It also shows your commitment and enthusiasm for the new role.\n\n3. **Documentation**: Bring any necessary documents for HR, such as identification for your I-9 form, banking information for direct deposit, and any other paperwork they might have requested.\n\n4. **Orientation**: Expect to go through an orientation process which may include an introduction to company policies, procedures, and culture. Pay close attention and take notes if needed.\n\n5. **Company Culture**: Universal has a vibrant and dynamic culture. Be prepared to immerse yourself in an environment that values creativity, teamwork, and exceptional customer service.\n\n6. **Training**: There will likely be training sessions to help you get acquainted with your role. Be patient, ask questions, and take advantage of these learning opportunities.\n\n7. **Meet Your Team**: You will probably meet your new colleagues and supervisors. Be friendly, introduce yourself, and make an effort to remember names and roles.\n\n8. **Workspace**: Get familiar with your workspace, whether it is in an office setting or within one of the parks. Know where essential facilities like restrooms, break rooms, and emergency exits are located.\n\n9. **Communication**: Understand the communication channels used within the company, such as email, internal messaging systems, or other tools.\n\n10. **Expectations**: Clarify your job expectations and responsibilities with your supervisor. Knowing what is expected of you will help you perform better and ease any initial anxiety.\n\n11. **Benefits and Perks**: Learn about the benefits and perks available to you as an employee, such as health insurance, discounts, and other employee programs.\n\n12. **Safety Protocols**: Familiarize yourself with the safety protocols and emergency procedures, especially if you are working in an environment that requires it.\n\n13. **Positive Attitude**: Bring a positive attitude and be ready to learn. Your willingness to adapt and grow will be crucial for your success at Universal.\n\nRemember, your first day is just the beginning. Take it one step at a time and try to absorb as much information as possible. Good luck!",
